{"author":{"id":"b35ffaad21059585d5d56824ce76c369324d531b5af7e79b2fef35def9e996d0"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1440191149,"nonce":"qwynWd/uB4LqMm4tdWM1ewj2cgI=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDEzMzU2MzY5Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/254#issuecomment-133563693"},"message":"@bgruening Yes, the box has openssl installed, and it looks like `package_ruby_2_0` compiled SSL support in:\n\n```\n$ find /path/to/tool_deps/ruby/2.0/iuc/package_ruby_2_0/b579f4987433 -name 'openssl.so' | xargs ldd\n    linux-vdso.so.1 =\u003e  (0x00007fff4c9fe000)\n    libssl.so.1.0.0 =\u003e /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libssl.so.1.0.0 (0x00007f45c5c7e000)\n    libcrypto.so.1.0.0 =\u003e /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libcrypto.so.1.0.0 (0x00007f45c58a3000)\n    libpthread.so.0 =\u003e /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libpthread.so.0 (0x00007f45c5684000)\n    libc.so.6 =\u003e /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6 (0x00007f45c52bf000)\n    libdl.so.2 =\u003e /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libdl.so.2 (0x00007f45c50bb000)\n    /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2 (0x00007f45c6138000)\n```\n\nIt looks like something distributed with this version of Ruby depends on SSLv2 (long paths to Ruby in tool_deps directory omitted):\n\n```\n$ ruby -ropenssl -e 'puts OpenSSL::OPENSSL_VERSION'\n[...]/lib/ruby/2.0.0/rubygems/core_ext/kernel_require.rb:55:in `require': [...]/lib/ruby/2.0.0/x86_64-linux/openssl.so: undefined symbol: SSLv2_method - [...]/lib/ruby/2.0.0/x86_64-linux/openssl.so (LoadError)\n    from [...]/lib/ruby/2.0.0/rubygems/core_ext/kernel_require.rb:55:in `require'\n    from [...]/lib/ruby/2.0.0/openssl.rb:17:in `\u003ctop (required)\u003e'\n    from [...]/lib/ruby/2.0.0/rubygems/core_ext/kernel_require.rb:55:in `require'\n    from [...]/lib/ruby/2.0.0/rubygems/core_ext/kernel_require.rb:55:in `require'\n```\n\nBut [Ubuntu doesn't compile SSLv2 into their libopenssl](http://stackoverflow.com/a/13472755). I don't know why I'd be the first to run into this problem though, so something else might be wrong!","files":null}]}